description: A HERO FOR HIRE GOES BAD! What drove Luke Cage’s old friend to a life of crime – and who are the forces out to destroy North Philadelphia? As Cage’s trip into his past continues, can he hold onto the man his family loves -- or will an old enemy push him over the edge?
name: The Land Where Killers Dwell

description: Move over Uncle Scrooge! The richest character in comic book history is about to get his due. Harvey Comics' original creation Richie Rich, the Poor Little Rich Boy, represented the fantasies of every comic book-loving kid growing up in the 1960s and 70s. Now, Dark Horse is delighted to present the ultimate tribute to the boy who has everything-and we mean everything! This mega compilation of the essential Richie collects his earliest and most substantial stories for the first time ever. Created by Sid Jacbson and Warren Kremer as a back-up feature in Little Dot comics in 1953, Richie Rich went on to become Harvey's biggest moneymaker, appearing in over fifty different spinoff titles over the next forty years. In addition to the magnificent comic art of Warren Kremer, Richie was also drawn by animation great Steve Muffatti and comics legend Ernie Colon.
name: Richie Rich the Poor Little Rich Boy
Lupo Alberto: Pugni, Bulli e... Pollastre!

description:
Newspaper comic strip reprints: Calvin and Hobbes, Batman, Modesty Blaise, The Phantom, Outland, Flash Gordon, Steve Canyon, and Bloom County.

Featuring the thrilling conclusion of the Penguin storyline! Batman thwarts the Penguin and saves the son of the Quraci ambassador, but it's not over yet! In desperation, the Penguin takes on a last-ditch hostage: District Attorney Harvey Dent's wife, Alice Dent! If Batman takes any risks to save Alice's life, nothing will stop Dent from personally declaring war on the vigilante!
name: Batman: The Penguin, part 4

description:
Newspaper comic strip reprints: Calvin and Hobbes, Batman, Modesty Blaise, The Phantom, Outland, Flash Gordon, and Steve Canyon (last new strip)

Bruce Wayne throws a birthday party for his best friend Harvey Dent, giving the District Attorney a special present: a silver two-headed coin! But the festivities are cut short when news hits of a riot at Gotham Penitentiary, releasing hundreds of prisoners onto the streets. Meanwhile, some influential Gotham citizens are fed up with the rampant crime, and are prepared to go extreme measures...
name: The Joker, part 1

description:
Newspaper comic strip reprints: Calvin and Hobbes, Batman, Modesty Blaise, The Phantom, Flash Gordon, Bloom County.

As a terrorist group steps up their assault on Gotham City, a businessman with ties to the group approaches Bruce Wayne and Harvey Dent, to see if they wish to pledge their support to "fighting" the terrorists. Fed up with vigilantes like Batman flaunting the law, Dent is sorely tempted to sell his soul, especially if it means support for an eventual Mayoral run. Bruce Wayne feigns enthusiastic interest to infiltrate the group, where he meets their leader known as the Red Hood... who, in reality, is the Joker!
name: Guess Who's Back
Il Lupo con Dentro la Gazza
Pepé Leccalecca
Quattro Lezioni D'amore

description: The startling conclusion to the origin of the Marvel Universe. Pearl Harbor, secret Nazi experiments gone wrong, and the seeds of destruction that would lead to the modern Marvel world of today will stand revealed! By the award-winning team of Ed Brubaker and Steve Epting.
name: Part Eight
Il Vero E Il Falso Strangolatore

description:
“The Saga of Bullseye Jonesy”: Yee-ha! It’s time to saddle up your horse and mosey into the old west for some rip-roaring fun! Lasso up some laughs with “Jonesy” and Chuck as the ride in to Peaceful Valley and try out to be Mayor Andrews’ new deputies!
“Treehouse Trouble”: Jughead and Archie are up a tree – literally, when they volunteer to build a treehouse for the Riverdale Boys and Girls Club!
“Food Mood”: An army travels on its stomach… and so does Jughead when he goes hiking… but is the backpack strong enough to hold all the sandwiches he had Betty make for his trip?
name: The Saga of Bullseye Jones

description: An all-new series from the star of NBC's PARKS & RECREATION and veteran comic scribes DeFilippis & Weir! Ariana Von Holmberg is an heiress with a secret. But what she's hiding isn't a sex tape or a drug addiction or an affair with a professional golfer—it's a new career as a CIA operative! What better cover for an agent than a globe-trotting, care-free femme with a penchant for flights of fancy? But can Ari balance her high society obligations with her new role as a spy or will the weight of two worlds bring her dual lives to a violent end?
name: Codename: Noob, Part One
I Due Volti De Candida
Cleo De Merode
Lapislazzulli Di Morte

And only Rima, the eyes of the jungle, knows what the heroes do not: something glorious and terrible has risen in the darkest corner of Hida`lgo!

description: When life takes us by surprise and makes everyone want to close their eyes, Brás finally gains something he’s been waiting his entire life to find. But he would trade it all to know what happened in Rio.
name: Chapter Six: 33

description: Studio Much to the dismay of J.D. Rockerduck's pocketbook, Scrooge and Donald's economic trek around the globe is coming to a close. Nothing can stop them now, except for maybe their women! Collect your pennies and pick up the finale to the story of greed and speed, 'Around the World in 80 Bucks.'
name: Around the World in 80 Bucks, Part 4

description:
Solicitation blurb: X-Man. Avenger. Soldier. And that's just the HALF of it. In this atomic-sized special, superstar David Finch leads a platoon of comic's most talented creators in giving the Canadian killer a 21-gun salute. Ninjas, bar-room brawls, Morlocks and pirates (yes, PIRATES!): this issue sees the most marvelous mutant of all put through the paces. And if five-all new tales of Snikt-tastic action wasn't enough, there's classic reprints featuring some of Logan's greatest hits!

First story: untitled.

Second story: The Curse of the Yellow Claw

Third story: Desperate Measures - The X-Men have come to the aid of the Morlocks, who are under attack by rogue Sentinels. Wolverine and Beast find themselves separated from the rest of their team and in the company of five Morlocks (Marrow, Ape, Matchstick Girl, Poser and Carapace). The last had been severely wounded while saving the inexperienced Poser from a Sentinel's blast, and the group are now running for shelter in the tunnels beneath Manhattan. Another blast from a Sentinel forces them into a dead end and collapses rubble, sealing them inside. Beast takes the opportunity to perform surgery on Cara (Carapace), using Wolverine's claws as scalpels, while the impatient Marrow is asked by Beast to try to find a way out. Half an hour later, Beast has succeeded in saving Cara's life. Meanwhile, Marrow forces an excessive amount of bone growth which she uses to ram the rubble, clearing a way out. Both Wolverine and Marrow ponder the fact that their respective mutations, typically used for attack and defense, had just been used as life-saving tools. [Note: this story takes place soon after X-Men Vol. 2 #75.]

Fourth story: One Night Only

Fifth story: Worst There Is

Sixth story: Birthday Boy

Seventh story: Puny Little Man [reprinted from Wolverine, Volume 3, #50.]

Eighth story: Hunger [reprinted from digital comic] After escaping the Weapon X facility where his bones had been laced with adamantium, Logan wanders the Canadian landscape, maddened by pain and hunger. He comes across a cabin where a young family lives. Before he makes a decision to accost them for food or to leave, he sees they are being approached by a pack of ravenous wolves. He leaps into the pack, slashing at them with his claws. After a bloody struggle, the pack runs off, leaving Logan face to face with the young couple and their two small children. Wielding an axe, the father prepares to defend his family against this savage stranger, but Logan turns and walks away. [Note: this story takes place soon after the Weapon X story arc in Marvel Comics Presents.]
name: The Curse Of The Yellow Claw; Desperate Measures; One Night Only; Worst There Is; Birthday Boy; Puny Little Man; Hunger

description: Space, the final frontier… and on that frontier and beyond, humans and aliens alike need medical care. Enter Leonard McCoy, Doctor of Space Medicine, late of the U.S.S. ENTERPRISE… his first assignment: save the human colonists from a mysterious plague on a distant world whose only native lifeform is a vast and suddenly hostile jungle. Shipped with a special variant Byrne “gag” cover!

description: Doctor McCoy hates mysterious ailments. He also hates the transporter. Now he finds himself on a world beset with one, where the only means of getting around is the other. John Byrne’s tale set in the period before Star Trek: The Motion Picture continues here with two covers from Byrne.
